checkpointRandao().details: Can be called by anyone. Takes a snapshot of the current randao to ensure unpredictable but deterministic      validator selection. Automatically called from setupEpoch. Can be used as a cheaper alternative to      `setupEpoch` to update the randao checkpoints.

claimProverRewards(address,uint256[]).details: Rewards must be enabled. Provers earn rewards for successfully proving epoch transitions.      Each epoch can only be claimed once per prover.

params._coinbase: The address that has accumulated the rewards - rewards are sent to this address
params._epochs: Array of epochs to claim rewards for

returns._0: The total amount of rewards claimed

claimSequencerRewards(address).details: Rewards must be enabled via isRewardsClaimable. Transfers all accumulated rewards to the recipient.

params._coinbase: The address that has accumulated the rewards - rewards are sent to this address

constructor.details: Sets up time parameters, deploys auxiliary contracts (slasher, reward booster),      initializes staking, validator selection, and creates inbox/outbox contracts

params._config: Comprehensive configuration including timing, staking, slashing, reward parameters, and unlock timestamp
params._epochProofVerifier: The honk verifier contract for root epoch proofs
params._feeAsset: The ERC20 token used for transaction fees
params._genesisState: Initial state containing VK tree root, protocol contracts hash, and genesis archive
params._stakingAsset: The ERC20 token used for validator staking

deposit(address,address,(uint256,uint256.details: The caller must have approved the staking asset. Validators enter a queue before becoming active.

params._attester: The address that will act as the validator (sign attestations)
params._moveWithLatestRollup: Whether to follow the chain if governance migrates to a new rollup version
params._proofOfPossession: The proof of possession to show that the keys in G1 and G2 share secret key
params._publicKeyInG1: The G1 point for the BLS public key (used for efficient signature verification in GSE)
params._publicKeyInG2: The G2 point for the BLS public key (used for BLS aggregation and pairing operations in GSE)
params._withdrawer: The address that can withdraw the stake

finalizeWithdraw(address).details: Can be called by anyone. Transfers the stake to the designated recipient.

params._attester: The validator address whose withdrawal to finalize

flushEntryQueue(uint256).details: Can be called by anyone. The number of validators added is limited by queue configuration.      This helps maintain a controlled growth rate of the validator set.

params._toAdd: - The max number the caller will try to add

getActiveAttesterCount().details: Active validators can propose checkpoints and participate in committees

returns._0: The count of validators in the active set

getEntryQueueFlushSize().details: Based on queue configuration and current validator set size. Used by flushEntryQueue.

returns._0: The number of validators that can be added in the next flush

initiateWithdraw(address,address).details: Starts the exit delay period. The validator is immediately removed from the active set.      Only the registered withdrawer can initiate withdrawal.

params._recipient: The address to receive the withdrawn stake

returns._0: True if withdrawal was initiated, false if already initiated

invalidateBadAttestation(uint256,(bytes,.details: Anyone can call this if they detect an invalid signature. This removes the checkpoint      and all subsequent checkpoints from the pending chain. Used to maintain pending chain integrity.

params._attestations: The attestations that were submitted with the checkpoint
params._committee: The committee members for the checkpoint's epoch
params._invalidIndex: The index of the invalid signature in the attestations

invalidateInsufficientAttestations(uint2.details: Anyone can call this if a checkpoint doesn't meet the required attestation threshold.      Even if all signatures are valid, checkpoints need a minimum number of attestations.

params._attestations: The attestations that were submitted with the checkpoint
params._committee: The committee members for the checkpoint's epoch

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

propose((bytes32,(int256),(bytes32,bytes.details: Core function for checkpoint production.      The attestations must include a signature from designated proposer to be accepted.      The checkpoint must build on the previous checkpoint and include valid attestations from committee members.      Failed proposals revert; successful ones emit CheckpointProposed and advance the chain state.      See ProposeLib#propose for more details.

params._args: checkpoint data including header, state updates, oracle inputs, and archive
params._attestations: Aggregated signatures from committee members attesting to checkpoint validity
params._blobInput: Blob commitment data for data availability (format: [numBlobs][48-byte commitments...])
params._signers: Addresses of committee members who signed (must match attestations)

prune().details: Can only be called after the proof submission window has expired for an epoch.      This maintains liveness by preventing the chain from being stuck on unproven checkpoints.      Pruning occurs at epoch boundaries and removes all checkpoints in unproven epochs.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

setLocalEjectionThreshold(uint256).details: Only callable by owner. The local ejection threshold is the minimum amount of stake that a validator can have      after being slashed.

setProvingCostPerMana(uint256).details: Only callable by owner. This affects how proving costs are calculated in the fee model.

params._provingCostPerMana: The cost in ETH per unit of mana for proving

setRewardConfig((address,uint32,address,.details: Only callable by the contract owner. Updates how rewards are calculated and distributed.

params._config: The new reward configuration including rates and booster settings

setRewardsClaimable(bool).details: Only callable by owner. This is a safety mechanism to control when rewards can be withdrawn.      Cannot set rewards as claimable before the earliest reward claimable timestamp.

params._isRewardsClaimable: True to enable reward claims, false to disable

setSlasher(address).details: Only callable by owner. The slasher handles punishment for validator misbehavior.

params._slasher: The address of the new slasher contract

setupEpoch().details: Can be called by anyone at the start of an epoch. Samples the committee and determines proposers for all      slots in the epoch. Also stores a seed that is used for future sampling. The corresponding library      functionality is automatically called when `RollupCore.propose(...)` is called (via the      `RollupOperationsExtLib.propose(...)` -> `ProposeLib.propose(...)` ->      `ValidatorSelectionLib.setupEpoch(...)`).      If there are missed proposals then setupEpoch does not get called automatically. Since the next committee      selection is computed based on the stored randao and the epoch number, failing to update the randao stored      will keep the committee predictable longer into the future. We would only fail to get a fresh randao if:      1. All the proposals in the epoch were missed      2. Nobody called setupEpoch on the Rollup contract      While an attacker might theoretically benefit from preventing a fresh seed (e.g. by DoSing all proposers),      preventing anyone from calling this function directly is not really feasible. This makes attacks on seed      generation impractical.

slash(address,uint256).details: Only callable by the authorized slasher contract. Reduces the validator's stake.

params._amount: The amount of stake to slash

submitEpochRootProof((uint256,uint256,(b.details: Proves the validity of a prefix of the checkpoints in an epoch. Once proven, checkpoints become final      and cannot be pruned. The proof must be submitted within the submission window.      Successful submission triggers prover rewards.

params._args: Contains the epoch range, public inputs, fees, attestations, and the ZK proof

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

updateEscapeHatch(address).details: Only callable by owner. Set to address(0) to disable escape hatch functionality.      The escape hatch provides an alternative block production path when the committee is unavailable.

params._escapeHatch: The address of the EscapeHatch contract, or address(0) to disable

updateL1GasFeeOracle().details: Automatically called during checkpoint proposal but can be called manually.      Updates the fee model's view of L1 costs to ensure accurate L2 fee pricing.      Uses current L1 gas price and blob gas price for calculations.

updateManaTarget(uint256).details: Only callable by owner. The new target must be greater than or equal to the current target      to avoid the ability for governance to use it directly to kill an old rollup.      Mana is the unit of computational work in Aztec.

params._manaTarget: The new target mana per slot

updateStakingQueueConfig((uint256,uint25.details: Only callable by owner. Controls how validators enter the active set.

params._config: New configuration including queue size limits and timing parameters

vote(uint256).details: This enables the rollup to participate in governance by voting on proposals.      See StakingLib.sol for more details on the voting mechanism.

params._proposalId: The ID of the proposal to vote on

L1_BLOCK_AT_GENESIS().notice: The L1 block number when this rollup was deployed

checkBlob().notice: Flag to enable/disable blob verification during simulations

checkpointRandao().notice: Captures the randao for future validator selection

invalidateInsufficientAttestations(uint2.notice: Invalidates a checkpoint due to insufficient valid attestations (>2/3 of committee required)

prune().notice: Removes unproven checkpoints from the pending chain

setProvingCostPerMana(uint256).notice: Updates the cost of proving per unit of mana

setRewardConfig((address,uint32,address,.notice: Updates the reward configuration for sequencers and provers

setupEpoch().notice: Sets up validator selection for the current epoch

slash(address,uint256).notice: Slashes a validator's stake for misbehavior

submitEpochRootProof((uint256,uint256,(b.notice: Submits a zero-knowledge proof for an epoch's state transition
